observations.recommendation:
We recommended, and Management agreed, that the LCE require:

(10) a. the MDRRMO to ensure proper monitoring on the utilization of LDRRMF and immediately communicate PPAs that are in need of funding;

(11) b. the Municipal Budget Officer to:

1.      ensure all disbursement are in accordance with the approved Annual Budget together with the LDRRMFIP and strictly monitor the availability of appropriation before the approval of an obligation;

2.      support any changes in the LDRRMFIP with augmentation, re-alignment, or supplemental budget, if any;

3.      prepare and maintain separate RAAOs for QRF, MOOE, and CO, in relation to the approved LDRRMFIP;

(12) c. Municipal Accountant to effect the necessary entries for the transfer of unspent balance and adjust the balance of Trust Liabilities-DRRM account at year-end;

(13) d. Municipal Treasurer to cause the complete transfer of unexpended balances of CY 2023 LDRRMF to the Trust Fund account.

We likewise recommended that the Municipal Mayor, Municipal Budget Officer, and MDRRMO refund the excess disbursements of 70% Mitigating Fund for CY 2023 totaling ₱359,895.00.

